itemListElement.name: Half-Day Private Tour of Snoqualmie Falls with Pick Up

name: Half-Day Private Tour of Snoqualmie Falls with Pick Up
description:
Firstly your private driver will pick you up in your desired place in Seattle. 

This can be your hotel or the cruise port. If arriving to the airport, an airport pick up can be done and then dropped off in Seattle or to the cruise port. 

We will drive to Snoqualmie Falls. Located 40 minutes outside of the city the falls are the most famous waterfall in Washington and most popular attraction. 

Snoqualmie Falls is a 268-foot (82 m) waterfall in the northwest United States, located east of Seattle on the Snoqualmie River between Snoqualmie and Fall City, Washington. It is one of Washington's most popular scenic attractions but is perhaps best known internationally for its appearance in the cult television series Twin Peaks.

After visiting the waterfall you will drive back to Seattle. This tour will finish at your hotel in Seattle.

Note that this tour is done with a driver only, not a tour guide.

name: Seattle Showdown Scavenger Hunt
description:
Our very unique, immersive adventures are the only ones of their kind. We, unlike other companies, provide your very own remote, interactive, live host to assist and encourage you along through your phone. We are an Austin, TX-based global custom event design company offering scavenger hunts and other events in 300+ cities in North America and beyond. Our specially hand-crafted adventures are equal parts tour, creative challenge, detective hunt, and social experiment! 

Guests get to discover in an alternate reality our favorite hidden gems off the beaten trail and creatively interpret fun art, history, and culture clues - for points! They get to enjoy fame and glory while appearing on our website’s international leaderboard, no matter what their score. They get to essentially race other teams in other cities, even if they don’t have competitors who have signed up in their city that day. Get ready to discover unusual oddities, laugh out loud, and make the experience your own!

review.name: So much LAUGHTER and FUN!!
review.reviewBody: We did our hunt in Victoria BC Canada.  We had so much fun!  All the information was forwarded to us just before and we went to the start location!  It is all easily walkable and we met so many people and had many laughs!  I would HIGHLY recommend to anyone in Victoria!  Great way to spend outlets afternoon!!  The organizers were engaged and cheered us on when we sent in our pics!  Soooo fun!  Great date or family afternoon!

review.name: Fun time!
review.reviewBody: We had a lot of fun! We loved the variety of things we had to find and complete. The hosts were readily available to troubleshoot any problems.

itemListElement.name: Seattle: Time Travel Exploration Game and Tour

name: Seattle: Time Travel Exploration Game and Tour
description:
Discover the iconic places that capture the innovative spirit of Seattle by solving clues and unlocking stories on your phone. Play the engaging exploration game to learn about the people whose dreams and forward-thinking created this unique city. 

As you solve challenges, the story unfolds and exact directions on your phone will guide you to the next location. You can play offline. Ready for an adventure?

Highlights include:
• Explore the Seattle Cloud Cover, Anne Frank Chestnut Tree, the Space Needle and lesser-known places.
• Enjoy a uniquely crafted story brought to you by our gifted writers.
• Learn about the thought pioneers whose ambitions and hard work shaped Seattle and the world.
• Walk through the city’s beautiful green spaces and parks, including the Olympic Sculpture Park and the Seattle Center
• Try a new type of experience, the perfect mix between a tour, outdoor escape game, and treasure hunt.

review.name: Cute little adventure
review.reviewBody: It was alright. You certainly get what you pay for. 100% my fault, but I've done self-guided tours like this in the past and expected something more based on the history and culture of the city. It's more (as it states) like a variety of puzzles and riddles that take you to some nice places in Downtown. I still had a lot of fun with it, and the app lets you get hints or directions if you need them. Since I was in a bit of a hurry, this came in handy as it helped me avoid taking too much time. One thing that made me feel uncomfortable was that one of the locales asked me to walk right into the center of a children's playground. As a 35 year old male with no kids...that felt inappropriate. The hint luckily helped me solve this part without having to walk into the  playground and I get that it's tough designing a tour that works for everyone though. Overall, if you've got an hour or two to kill, it's a nice time-killer, especially for the price.

review.name: Very fun tour!
review.reviewBody: This was a delightful way to learn about how the 1962 Worlds Fair impacted Seattle and how the impacts are lasting to this day. There are many stops along this tour that will make you want to enjoy other attractions (and feel free to do so). We decided to complete the walk and make notes of things we would love to do for our next Seattle trip. All of the puzzles are easy to understand and manage. This really takes as long as you want it to depending on your walking speed, ingenuity and puzzle-solving prowess, and willingness to continue. A very fun way to spend some time outdoors with family, friends, or solo and explore such a beautiful city.

review.name: Scavenger hunt on a rainy Seattle day
review.reviewBody: Well organized. Good exercise if both mind and body. The game creators have chosen landmarks and plaques that are permanent and easy to find but not as easy to solve.

review.name: Amazingly Fun Time
review.reviewBody: We really enjoyed walking about the city of Seattle while using your walking tour app.  We found things in the city we may not have discovered.  I would highly recommend your app if you are unsure of what to do upon arrival in a new destination. We plan to return to some of the places to relax/explore further during our stay.  The price to use the self-guided walking tour was well worth the journey.

review.name: Gives a great overview of the area
review.reviewBody: We enjoyed this walking tour a lot - it gave a great overview of the area with plenty of knowledge to be learned. Found some hidden gems too which would have remained hidden if we hadn’t done the tour!   The clues were a bit tricky at times, but the option to get a hint usually solved it!  You can go at your own pace and it took us about an hour and a half.   Will definitely do another as these appear to be in lots of cities.

review.name: Self guided tour worth the time
review.reviewBody: We had a blast the clues were imaginative and just tricky enough to give us a pause.  Very fun. Learned some cool stuff and some hidden points of interest I really hadn't noticed before.

review.name: Seattle Center Experience
review.reviewBody: This tour was delightful. The visited sites were beautiful and historically significant. Layout and route was well thought out. The storyline, clues, and games were a perfect balance of whimsical fun and satisfying information. Well done. Still smiling.
